<article doi="10.15252/embj.201798449"><fig id="24292"><title>: JARID2 exists as a LMW form (~80kDa) in many cell types.</title><label>Figure 1</label><graphic href="https://api.sourcedata.io/file.php?figure_id=24292"/><sd-panel panel_id="64407">A schematic diagram showing functional domains of <sd-pretag id="sdPretag1656469125sm" type="geneprod" role="assayed">JARID2</sd-pretag>: UIM, <sd-pretag id="sdPretag678774463sm" type="geneprod" role="assayed">ubiquitin</sd-pretag> interaction motif; transcription repressive domain consisting of sub-domains 1-3; <sd-pretag id="sdPretag1959588002sm" type="geneprod" role="assayed">JmjN</sd-pretag>, JumonjiN; ARID, AT-rich <sd-pretag id="sdPretag1499626960sm" type="molecule" role="component">DNA</sd-pretag> binding domain; <sd-pretag id="sdPretag586835713sm" type="geneprod" role="assayed">GSGFP</sd-pretag> which is a <sd-pretag id="sdPretag2033911143sm" type="geneprod" role="assayed">SUZ12</sd-pretag> binding domain; JmjC, JumonjiC; and ZF, zinc finger domain. <strong>Domains 1-3 constitute <sd-pretag id="sdPretag1033330918sm" type="geneprod" role="assayed">PRC2</sd-pretag> associated domains. Domain 1 is required for <sd-pretag id="sdPretag1346894822sm" type="geneprod" role="intervention">PRC2</sd-pretag> stimulation, domain 2 is needed for binding to <sd-pretag id="sdPretag1257842915sm" type="geneprod" role="component">EZH2</sd-pretag> and domain 3 is needed for <sd-pretag id="sdPretag2062591424sm" type="subcellular" role="component">nucleosomal</sd-pretag> binding. The RNA binding domain has been indicated with dashed box.</strong> <graphic href="https://api.sourcedata.io/file.php?panel_id=64407"/></sd-panel><sd-panel panel_id="64408"><sd-tag id="sdTag1" source="sdapi" category="assay" entity_type="None" role="None" text="Immunoblot" ext_ids="BAO_0002422" ext_dbs="" in_caption="True" ext_names="immunoblot" ext_tax_ids="" ext_tax_names="" ext_urls="https://bioportal.bioontology.org/ontologies/BAO/?p=classes&amp;conceptid=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.bioassayontology.org%2Fbao%23">Immunoblot</sd-tag> of whole cell lysates from multiple <sd-tag id="sdTag2" source="sdapi" category="None" entity_type="organism" role="component" text="human" ext_ids="9606" ext_dbs="" in_caption="True" ext_names="Homo sapiens" ext_tax_ids="" ext_tax_names="" ext_urls="http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/taxonomy/">human</sd-tag> lineage-committed cell-lines using a C-terminal anti-<sd-tag id="sdTag3" source="sdapi" category="None" entity_type="protein" role="assayed" text="JARID2" ext_ids="Q92833" ext_dbs="" in_caption="True" ext_names="JARID2" ext_tax_ids="9606" ext_tax_names="Homo sapiens" ext_urls="https://www.uniprot.org/uniprot/">JARID2</sd-tag> antibody. The size of canonical form is 140kDa but an additional strong band was detected at around ~80kDa. The <sd-tag id="sdTag4" source="sdapi" category="assay" entity_type="None" role="None" text="blot" ext_ids="BAO_0002422" ext_dbs="" in_caption="True" ext_names="immunoblot" ext_tax_ids="" ext_tax_names="" ext_urls="https://bioportal.bioontology.org/ontologies/BAO/?p=classes&amp;conceptid=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.bioassayontology.org%2Fbao%23">blot</sd-tag> is divided according to cell-types, which are indicated in the figure. <graphic href="https://api.sourcedata.io/file.php?panel_id=64408"/></sd-panel><sd-panel panel_id="64409"><sd-tag id="sdTag18" source="sdapi" category="assay" entity_type="None" role="None" text="qPCR" ext_ids="BAO_0003031" ext_dbs="" in_caption="True" ext_names="quantitative PCR" ext_tax_ids="" ext_tax_names="" ext_urls="https://bioportal.bioontology.org/ontologies/BAO/?p=classes&amp;conceptid=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.bioassayontology.org%2Fbao%23">qPCR</sd-tag> measurements of <sd-tag id="sdTag19" source="sdapi" category="None" entity_type="gene" role="assayed" text="JARID2" ext_ids="3720" ext_dbs="" in_caption="True" ext_names="JARID2" ext_tax_ids="9606" ext_tax_names="Homo sapiens" ext_urls="http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/gene/">JARID2</sd-tag> mRNA levels in different cell lines. The RNA levels were measured relative to 18S rRNA. Means and SEs are calculated over at least 2 independent experiments and 3 technical replicates. The data is represented as mean Â± SE. <graphic href="https://api.sourcedata.io/file.php?panel_id=64409"/></sd-panel><sd-panel panel_id="64410"><sd-tag id="sdTag38" source="sdapi" category="assay" entity_type="None" role="None" text="Immunoblot" ext_ids="BAO_0002422" ext_dbs="" in_caption="True" ext_names="immunoblot" ext_tax_ids="" ext_tax_names="" ext_urls="https://bioportal.bioontology.org/ontologies/BAO/?p=classes&amp;conceptid=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.bioassayontology.org%2Fbao%23">Immunoblot</sd-tag> showing that the ~80kDa band disappears upon treatment of <sd-tag id="sdTag39" source="sdapi" category="None" entity_type="cell" role="experiment" text="HEK293T" ext_ids="CVCL_0063" ext_dbs="" in_caption="True" ext_names="HEK293T" ext_tax_ids="9606" ext_tax_names="Homo sapiens" ext_urls="https://identifiers.org/cellosaurus:">HEK293T</sd-tag> and <sd-tag id="sdTag40" source="sdapi" category="None" entity_type="cell" role="experiment" text="HaCaT" ext_ids="CVCL_0038" ext_dbs="" in_caption="True" ext_names="HaCaT" ext_tax_ids="9606" ext_tax_names="Homo sapiens" ext_urls="https://identifiers.org/cellosaurus:">HaCaT</sd-tag> cells with siRNAs against exon 3 and exon 15 of <sd-tag id="sdTag41" source="sdapi" category="None" entity_type="gene" role="intervention" text="JARID2" ext_ids="3720" ext_dbs="" in_caption="True" ext_names="JARID2" ext_tax_ids="9606" ext_tax_names="Homo sapiens" ext_urls="http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/gene/">JARID2</sd-tag> RNA. Non-silencing control (NSC) was used as a transfection control. <graphic href="https://api.sourcedata.io/file.php?panel_id=64410"/></sd-panel></fig><fig id="24293"><title>: JARID2 LMW is a cleaved product of full length JARID2 isofrom-1.</title><label>Figure 2</label><graphic href="https://api.sourcedata.io/file.php?figure_id=24293"/><sd-panel panel_id="64411">A schematic show